    },
    {
      "id": "e5f6a7b8-5555-4000-8000-000000000008",
      "name": "Build Success Response",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 3,
      "position": [1250, 100],
      "parameters": {
        "language": "javaScript",
        "code": "return [{\n  json: {\n    status: 'success',\n    message: 'Operation completed successfully via retry pattern.',\n    timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),\n    execution_id: $execution.id\n  }\n}];"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "e5f6a7b8-5555-4000-8000-000000000009",
      "name": "Build Failure Response",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 3,
      "position": [1500, 450],
      "parameters": {
        "language": "javaScript",
        "code": "return [{\n  json: {\n    status: 'failed',\n    message: 'Operation failed after all retries and fallback. Routed to dead-letter queue.',\n    timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),\n    execution_id: $execution.id,\n    dead_letter: true,\n    fallback_attempted: true\n  }\n}];"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "e5f6a7b8-5555-4000-8000-000000000010",
      "name": "Master Pattern: Production Error Handler",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [200, -50],
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Production Error Handler (Master Workflow)\n\n**Purpose:** Orchestrates all 4 error handling patterns into one integrated system.\n\n**Flow:**\n1. **Webhook** receives the operation request\n2. **Retry with Backoff** attempts the operation (up to 3 retries)\n3. **Check result:**\n   - **Success path:** Log audit → return success response\n   - **Failure path:** Try fallback → log to dead-letter queue → log audit → return failure response\n4. **Audit logging** runs on BOTH paths (always)\n\n**Setup:**\nSet these environment variables in n8n:\n- `RETRY_WORKFLOW_ID` → ID of retry-with-backoff workflow\n- `FALLBACK_WORKFLOW_ID` → ID of fallback-path workflow\n- `DEAD_LETTER_WORKFLOW_ID` → ID of dead-letter-queue workflow\n- `AUDIT_WORKFLOW_ID` → ID of audit-logging workflow\n\nOr replace the expressions with hardcoded workflow IDs.",
        "width": 450,
        "height": 380
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "e5f6a7b8-5555-4000-8000-000000000011",
      "name": "Flow Diagram",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [700, -50],
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Flow Diagram\n\n```\nWebhook\n  │\n  ▼\nRetry with Backoff\n  │\n  ├─ SUCCESS ──► Audit Log ──► Success Response\n  │\n  └─ FAILURE\n       │\n       ▼\n     Fallback Path\n       │\n       ▼\n     Dead Letter Queue\n       │\n       ▼\n     Audit Log ──► Failure Response\n```\n\nEvery path logs an audit record. No silent failures.",
        "width": 350,
        "height": 280
      }
    }
  ],
